reviewText: I remember when I first saw this on PBS In Madison, WI and have been thinking of obtaining it ever since. It makes me proud to be a Wisconsinite.

1992 program uses interviews with an historian and veterans to cover WW2, the Korean war, the collision with DD-510 Eaton. mothballing, the Reagan era refit, the Iraq war, and the final decommissioning in 1991.  This was ten years before being opened as a museum.
Interesting video I had seen on TV. My father-in-law served on the USS Wisconsin in WWII. He enjoyed the video and had many interesting stories to add.
